<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-02-10T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-02-10T14:00:00-05:00" n="666" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d666">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79620 Boeing Airplane Co./19:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-10T14:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            10, 1928—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>8. Your 10, February 9, 6 p.m. (1) Yes, if invited to do so. (2) Date
                                of arrival will be communicated to you by Embassy at Rio de Janeiro.
                                (3) He plans to fly from Rio de Janeiro to Buenos Aires and thence
                                to Santiago in order to demonstrate capabilities of machines.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olds</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>